<section id="To_create_a_method_in_the_FactoryService_Class2" remap="TID_15586">
	<title>Creating a Method in the Service Class</title>
	<para>
		Service methods have been split based on purpose.
	</para>
	<procedure>
		<title>To Create a Method in the Service Class</title>
		<step>
			<para>
				Navigate to <menuchoice><guimenu>Automate</guimenu><guisubmenu>Explorer</guisubmenu></menuchoice>.
			</para>
		</step> 
		<!--<step>
			<para>
				Click the <guilabel>Datastore</guilabel> accordion, and select a <menuchoice><guimenu>Factory</guimenu><guisubmenu>Service</guisubmenu></menuchoice> class.
			</para>
		</step>-->
		<step>
			<para>
				Service Class is located at <menuchoice><guimenu>DOMAIN</guimenu><guisubmenu>Service</guisubmenu><guimenuitem>Provisioning</guimenuitem><guimenuitem>StateMachines</guimenuitem><guimenuitem>Methods</guimenuitem></menuchoice> and <menuchoice><guimenu>Domain</guimenu><guisubmenu>Service</guisubmenu><guimenuitem>Retirement</guimenuitem><guimenuitem>StateMachines</guimenuitem><guimenuitem>Methods</guimenuitem></menuchoice>.
			</para>
			<note>
				<para>
					DOMAIN must be a user-defined Domain and not the locked ManageIQ Domain. If necessary, you can copy the class from the ManageIQ domain into a custom domain.
				</para>
			</note>
		</step>
		<step>
			<para>
				Click the <guilabel>Methods</guilabel> tab.
			</para>
		</step>
		<step>
			<para>
				Click 
				<inlinemediaobject>
					<imageobject>
						<imagedata fileref="images/1847.png" />
					</imageobject>
				</inlinemediaobject><guilabel>(Configuration)</guilabel>, then 
				<inlinemediaobject>
					<imageobject>
						<imagedata fileref="images/2360.png" />
					</imageobject>
				</inlinemediaobject> <guilabel>(Add a New Method)</guilabel>.
			</para>
		</step>
		<step>
			<para>
				Type in a <guilabel>Name</guilabel> and <guilabel>Display Name</guilabel>.
			</para>
		</step>
		<step>
			<para>
				In the <guilabel>Data</guilabel> field, type in the method contents.
			</para>
		</step>
		<step>
			<para>
				Click <guibutton>Validate</guibutton> and wait for your data entry to be successfully validated.
			</para>
		</step>
		<step>
			<para>
				Click <guibutton>Add</guibutton>.
			</para>
		</step>
	</procedure>
	<mediaobject>
		<imageobject>
			<imagedata align="center" fileref="images/6297.png" />
		</imageobject>
	</mediaobject>
</section>